{"questionId":"33603611","questionHtml":"<p>Given that a <em>MyLife</em> user chosen at random is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn></math> years or older, find the probability that they are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>65</mn></math> years or older.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition of conditional probability in context<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>65</mn><mo>|</mo><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>45</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>∩</mo><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>65</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>45</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Recognition must be shown in context either in words or symbols, not just <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>|</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>65</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mtext>age</mtext><mo>≥</mo><mn>45</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></m